---
title: Creamy White Bean, Pork & Kale Soup with Pearl Pasta, Thyme & Parmesan
description: Hearty and flavorful, this one-pot soup comes together fast! You’ll brown ground pork with aromatic thyme and garlic, stir in silky cannellini beans, fresh kale, and bouncy pearl pasta, then simmer until the flavor meld. A finishing swirl of crème fraîche adds velvety texture, and a sprinkle of nutty Parmesan cheese brings the whole bowl together.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6627cb1d2fa454163f21187b-ce6439ae.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6627cb1d2fa454163f21187b-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
cuisine: Southern Europe
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1390 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-white-bean-pork-kale-soup-6627cb1d2fa454163f21187b
time required: 20 minutes
---

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and season with @dried thyme{1%tsp},
@garlic powder{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up
meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

While pork cooks, wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%unit}. Remove and discard any large
stems from @kale{4%ounce}.

To pot with pork, add beans, @chicken stock concentrate{3%unit}, and
3 cups water (6 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then
reduce to a low simmer.

Stir in kale and @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
kale is wilted and couscous is tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @crème fraîche{2%tbsp}. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide soup between bowls. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} and
serve.

> TIP: If you have a lemon on hand, squeeze some over top for added flavor!

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.